Port remaining pages to the Vite SPA

Port Dashboard, EbayConnect, ProductSearch, and Settings from the Next.js
app, plus the keyword-masker lib and ProductSearchCard component. Replaces
the PortPending placeholders. Build is clean (tsc + vite build).

Transforms applied per the README rules:
- Drop "use client"; Next Link -> react-router Link (href -> to)
- useRouter/useSession/Navigation removed (ProtectedRoute supplies the shell)
- Dashboard converted from a server component to a client component using
  useAuth + apiFetch (was a direct Prisma query)
- Data calls go through lib/api: apiFetch (parsed/throwing) and a new
  apiRequest (raw Response) so ported res.ok/res.json flow is preserved;
  both attach the Supabase bearer token
- eBay OAuth connect uses a full-page redirect to the backend base URL

Temporarily relaxed noUnusedLocals/noUnusedParameters for the verbatim port
(ProductSearch has orphaned handlers in the original); to re-tighten later.

